    "en": {
      "title": "Two prison inmates pass A-level",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "According to the prison portal, two prisoners, including LTTE inmates of the special category who appeared for the Merawa High Level examination, have passed.",
        "Prison Media Spokesman, Control and Rehabilitation Commissioner Mr. Chandana Ekanayake said that three prisoners appeared in the examination center of Magazine Prison in the subject stream this year.",
        "The prison media spokesman said that with the full intervention of the prison department, the prisoners were presented for examination with the main objective of rehabilitating the inmates who are sent to prison on various charges and making them socialize as good citizens.",
        "The 38-year-old resident of Kilinochchi area, a special category LTTE detainee who appeared for the examination, passed in Geography - Honors Pass C, Hindu Civilization - Honors Pass C and Tamil Language - General Pass S The prison media spokesperson said that there has been.",
        "He said that the 46-year-old detainee, a resident of Kegalle, who appeared from Welikada prison, had obtained and passed Political Science-General Pass S, Buddhist Civilization-General Pass S, and Sinhala-General Pass S."
      ],
